<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-21T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01 American Military Government/9a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-21T13:00:00-04:00">January
                                    21, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>512. For your information, the British Embassy has informed the
                            Department that Mr. Strang proposed to bring before the Commission the
                            paper on Civil Affairs in France dated October 6, and desired to <pb facs="0032" n="22" xml:id="pg_22"/> suggest at the same time that
                            the Committee adopt a recommendation that the whole question of French
                            Civil Affairs be discussed with the French Committee. The Embassy was
                            informed that we could give no approval to such a recommendation, and it
                            was suggested that the Commission take note of the paper without making
                            any recommendation as to methods of carrying it out.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>